The paper deals with algorithms for efficiently processing queries on a set of points, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of data structures to preprocess the points suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS). The problem of identifying the smallest color spanning object can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper may also be relevant to databases (cs.DB) due to the focus on efficient query processing. Finally, the use of algorithms to solve the problem suggests that the paper may be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
